    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nAfter making changes to a file, the start/end lines of the folds are not always correct.  I have attached a screencast demonstrating different cases that I could observe: \r\n\r\n(Updated screencast using `nvim --clean`) \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/639806/fad1f3b8-e1ee-4234-932b-f87f6897437c\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n 1. Copy to `~/Downloads/folds.lua`:\r\n ```lua \r\nvim.treesitter.start()\r\n\r\nvim.opt.foldlevel = 99\r\nvim.opt.foldlevelstart = 99\r\nvim.opt.foldenable = true \r\nvim.opt.number = true \r\nvim.opt.foldcolumn = '1' \r\nvim.opt.foldmethod = 'expr' \r\nvim.opt.foldexpr = 'v:lua.vim.treesitter.foldexpr()' \r\nvim.opt.foldtext = 'v:lua.vim.treesitter.foldtext()'\r\nvim.opt.fillchars = { fold = ' ' }\r\n\r\nvim.cmd([[au WinNew,BufWinEnter * exec 'normal! zx'|exec 'normal! zR']])\r\nvim.cmd('normal! zx')\r\nvim.cmd('normal! zR')\r\n\r\n\r\nfunction test()\r\nend\r\n```\r\n2.  nvim --clean   \r\n3. e ~/Downloads/folds.lua\r\n4. so % \r\n5. Watch the recording for different cases\r\n\r\n(Updated the above to use `nvim --clean` as per the [comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/26224#issuecomment-1826759554))\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe folds should be correct.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-38e9875\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nn/a\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux x86_64 6.2.0-37-generic #38~22.04.1-Ubuntu \r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.30.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nappimage (nightly)",
